sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K566006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
Sequence of pCpcG2 promoter was obtained from pJT122 plasmid of Dr. Jeff Tabor. Rest of the sequences were obtained from the Registry.
Complete construction was synthesized.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Potential and gate.
Composed of pCpcG2 promoter which may be inducible by green light, this way it express penI and this represses mnt expression, allowing the transcription of any gene controlled under pMnt promoter.
This construction may be used with another one which represses mnt expression with red light and this way it may act as an and-gate.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Search for illegal sites was performed, they were found and removed.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel Rodriguez and Porfirio Quintero

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Mnt opt
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Mnt repressor optimized for E. coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Original sequence was taken from BioBrick BBa_C0072, this was optimized with preferential codons for better expression into E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Mnt repressor optimized with preferential codons for better expression into E. coli.
This protein acts as a negative regulator for pMnt promoter (BBa_R0073)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Search for illegal sites was performed, they were found and removed.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel Rodriguez

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pCpcG2 inv
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: pCpcG2 promoter, inverted sequence (Green light inducible)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Sequence was obtained from pJT122 plasmid of Dr. Jeff Tabor, but it was synthesized.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
pCpcG2 promoter (inverted sequence) from pJT122 plasmid of Dr. Jeff Tabor.
This promoter is inducible with green light through ccaR and ccaS photoreceptor system.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Search for illegal sites was performed, no sites were found.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel Rodriguez

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PenI inv
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: PenI repressor optimized for E. coli (inverted sequence)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Original sequence was taken from Registry (BBa_C0074), this was optimized with preferential codons for better expression in E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
PenI repressor with codon optimization for improving expression into E. coli.
This protein represents a negative repressor for pPenI promoter (BBa_R0074).
Sequence was inverted for simplifying DNA synthesis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Search for illegal sites was performed, they were found and eliminated.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel Rodriguez

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PenI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: PenP operator from Bacillus Lichenformis. Two operator sites are negatively regulated by PenI (C0074).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: crackdots
